Microsoft provides built‑in Azure Policies specifically for this.
Built‑in Policy (what you want)
Name: Configure Microsoft Defender CSPM to be enabled
Policy ID: 689f7782-ef2c-4270-a6d0-7664869076bd
Effect: DeployIfNotExists
What it does

Automatically sets:
Microsoft.Security/pricings
name = "CloudPosture"
pricingTier = "Standard"

Enforces CSPM at management group or subscription scope
Ensures future subscriptions inherit CSPM automatically

How to assign the policy (recommended setup)
Scope: Management Group (best for enterprise governance)

Steps

Azure Portal → Policy
Definitions
Search: Configure Microsoft Defender CSPM
Assign policy
Set effect = DeployIfNotExists
Managed Identity = System-assigned
Assign at MG root

Required role: Owner (policy will deploy Defender pricing)

Microsoft explicitly states:

1. CSPM plans are subscription-level
2. Azure Policy is supported and recommended to enforce enablement
3. Secure Score is subscription-scoped but visible at management group
